      "description": "Practical Programming (compressed week) — stress day.\n\nDeadlift (primary stress)\n- Warm-up to top set\n- 152.5 kg x5 (top set)\n- 137.5 kg x5 (backoff ~90%)\n\nBench Press (volume)\n- 81 kg, 5x5\n\nCable Chins\n- 4x8-10 (add load only when all sets hit 10 clean reps)\n\nOptional Cable Row\n- 2x12 moderate\n\nProgression rules (PP)\n- Deadlift: add +2.5 kg next week only if top set is technically solid (no lumbar flexion drift).\n- Bench: add +1 kg next bench exposure only if 5x5 completed with stable bar speed.\n- If deadlift or bench misses target reps, repeat same load next exposure.\n\nLOG\n16-3-26\nDeadlift:\n60kg 5,5, 85kg 5, 110kg 3, 130kg 2, 152.5kg 5, 137.5kg 5,\nBench:\n20kg 5,5, 40kg 5, 55kg 3, 70kg 2, 81kg 5,5,5,5,5\nChins:\n70kg 10, 75kg 10,10,8 (last set, couldn’t do another rep)",
